name: COUNTIF
description: Counts the rows where a condition is true.

name: CORR
description: Calculates the correlation coefficient of a set of numbers.

name: COVAR_POP
description: Calculates the population covariance of a set of numbers.

name: COVAR_SAMP
description: Calculates the sample covariance of a set of numbers.

name: STDDEV_POP
description: Calculates the population standard deviation of a set of numbers.

name: STDDEV_SAMP
description: Calculates the sample standard deviation of a set of numbers.

name: VAR_POP
description: Calculates the population variance of a set of numbers.

name: VAR_SAMP
description: Calculates the sample variance of a set of numbers.

name: BIT_AND
description: Returns the bitwise AND of non-NULL input values.

name: BIT_OR
description: Returns the bitwise OR of non-NULL input values.

name: BIT_XOR
description: Returns the bitwise XOR of non-NULL input values.

name: ANY_VALUE
description: Returns any arbitrary value from the input values.

name: ARRAY_AGG
description: Aggregates values into an array.

name: STRING_AGG
description: Aggregates string values with a delimiter.

name: COUNT
description: Counts the number of rows.

name: MAX
description: Returns the maximum value.

name: MIN
description: Returns the minimum value.

name: SUM
description: Returns the sum of values.

name: AVG
description: Returns the average of values.

name: ACOS
description: Returns the arccosine of a number.

name: ASIN
description: Returns the arcsine of a number.

name: ATAN
description: Returns the arctangent of a number.

name: ATAN2
description: Returns the arctangent of two numbers.

name: COS
description: Returns the cosine of a number.

name: COSH
description: Returns the hyperbolic cosine of a number.

name: SIN
description: Returns the sine of a number.

name: SINH
description: Returns the hyperbolic sine of a number.

name: TAN
description: Returns the tangent of a number.

name: TANH
description: Returns the hyperbolic tangent of a number.

name: GREATEST
description: Returns the greatest value in a list of expressions.

name: LEAST
description: Returns the least value in a list of expressions.

name: NULLIFZERO
description: Returns NULL if the input is zero.

name: ZEROIFNULL
description: Returns zero if the input is NULL.

name: FORMAT
description: Formats values into a string.

name: LPAD
description: Pads a string on the left to a certain length.

name: RPAD
description: Pads a string on the right to a certain length.

name: LEFT
description: Returns a substring from the beginning of a string.

name: RIGHT
description: Returns a substring from the end of a string.

name: STARTS_WITH
description: Returns TRUE if the string starts with the specified prefix.

name: ENDS_WITH
description: Returns TRUE if the string ends with the specified suffix.

name: ARRAY_LENGTH
description: Returns the length of an array.

name: ARRAY_REVERSE
description: Reverses the elements in an array.

name: ARRAY_CONCAT
description: Concatenates multiple arrays into one.

name: ARRAY_TO_STRING
description: Converts an array to a single string.

name: GENERATE_ARRAY
description: Generates an array of values in a range.

name: GENERATE_DATE_ARRAY
description: Generates an array of dates in a range.

name: PARSE_TIMESTAMP
description: Parses a timestamp from a string.

name: STRING_TO_ARRAY
description: Splits a string into an array of substrings.

name: SAFE_DIVIDE
description: Divides two numbers, returning NULL if the divisor is zero.

name: SAFE_MULTIPLY
description: Multiplies two numbers, returning NULL if an overflow occurs.

name: SAFE_ADD
description: Adds two numbers, returning NULL if an overflow occurs.

name: SAFE_SUBTRACT
description: Subtracts two numbers, returning NULL if an overflow occurs.

name: ABS
description: Returns the absolute value of a number.

name: CEIL
description: Rounds up to the nearest integer.

name: FLOOR
description: Rounds down to the nearest integer.

name: ROUND
description: Rounds to the specified number of decimal places.

name: TRUNC
description: Truncates to the specified number of decimal places.

name: POW
description: Returns a number raised to a power.

name: SQRT
description: Returns the square root of a number.

name: LOG
description: Returns the natural logarithm of a number.

name: LOG10
description: Returns the base-10 logarithm of a number.

name: CONCAT
description: Concatenates two or more strings.

name: LOWER
description: Converts a string to lowercase.

name: UPPER
description: Converts a string to uppercase.

name: TRIM
description: Removes leading and trailing whitespace.

name: LTRIM
description: Removes leading whitespace.

name: RTRIM
description: Removes trailing whitespace.

name: LENGTH
description: Returns the length of a string.

name: REGEXP_CONTAINS
description: Returns TRUE if the string contains a match for the regex.

name: REGEXP_EXTRACT
description: Extracts the first match of the regex from the string.

name: REGEXP_REPLACE
description: Replaces all matches of the regex with a replacement string.

name: SUBSTR
description: Returns a substring.

name: CAST
description: Converts a value to a different data type.

name: SAFE_CAST
description: Converts a value to a different data type, returning NULL on error.

name: CURRENT_DATE
description: Returns the current date.

name: DATE_ADD
description: Adds a specified interval to a date.

name: DATE_SUB
description: Subtracts a specified interval from a date.

name: DATE_DIFF
description: Returns the difference between two dates.

name: DATE_TRUNC
description: Truncates a date to a specified granularity.

name: TIMESTAMP_ADD
description: Adds a specified interval to a timestamp.

name: TIMESTAMP_SUB
description: Subtracts a specified interval from a timestamp.

name: TIMESTAMP_DIFF
description: Returns the difference between two timestamps.

name: TIMESTAMP_TRUNC
description: Truncates a timestamp to a specified granularity.

name: FORMAT_DATE
description: Formats a date according to the specified format string.

name: FORMAT_TIMESTAMP
description: Formats a timestamp according to the specified format string.

name: PARSE_DATE
description: Parses a date from a string.

name: NTILE
description: Divides rows into a specified number of buckets and assigns a bucket number.

name: PERCENT_RANK
description: Calculates the percent rank of a value in a partition.

name: CUME_DIST
description: Calculates the cumulative distribution of a value in a partition.

name: NTH_VALUE
description: Returns the nth value in a window partition.

name: PERCENTILE_CONT
description: Computes a continuous percentile of a value.

name: PERCENTILE_DISC
description: Computes a discrete percentile of a value.

name: ROW_NUMBER
description: Returns the sequential row number.

name: RANK
description: Returns the rank with gaps.

name: DENSE_RANK
description: Returns the rank without gaps.

name: LAG
description: Returns the value from a previous row.

name: LEAD
description: Returns the value from a subsequent row.

name: FIRST_VALUE
description: Returns the first value in the window frame.

name: LAST_VALUE
description: Returns the last value in the window frame.
